{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"8bf4403c-af35-459b-a822-6f32fd0d98c0","content":"In .NET MAUI, you use **lifecycle event mappings** configured in `MauiProgram.cs` via `ConfigureLifecycleEvents`:\n\n```csharp\nusing Microsoft.Maui.LifecycleEvents;\n\nbuilder.ConfigureLifecycleEvents(events =>\n{\n#if ANDROID\n    events.AddAndroid(android => android\n        .OnPause(activity =>\n        {\n            // runs when activity is pausing\n        })\n        .OnStop(activity =>\n        {\n            // runs when activity is no longer visible\n        }));\n#endif\n\n#if IOS\n    events.AddiOS(ios => ios\n        .DidEnterBackground(app =>\n        {\n            // runs when app enters background\n        }));\n#endif\n});\n```\n\n**Key points:**\n\n- Add `using Microsoft.Maui.LifecycleEvents;`\n- Use `#if ANDROID` / `#if IOS` preprocessor directives to keep platform code conditional.\n- Each platform exposes its native lifecycle events (e.g., `OnResume`, `OnDestroy` for Android; `WillEnterForeground`, `WillTerminate` for iOS).\n- This approach keeps everything in one place without needing custom platform projects or renderers.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"13afac78-909a-40b7-b187-d17c79bc5a51","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about how to hook into platform-specific lifecycle events in .NET MAUI - specifically Android's OnPause/OnStop and iOS's DidEnterBackground. This is a knowledge question about .NET MAUI development, not a code task in the repository. I'll answer directly from my knowledge.","outputTokens":387,"requestId":"483F:386B3C:53C2BF0:5BE6CCF:69F3FAD5"},"id":"2f0e291e-1871-496c-ad6e-3dec420d948a","timestamp":"2026-05-01T00:59:09.349Z","parentId":"96bb99c1-62e7-49be-a26f-b74dfdc58582"}
